vine 1.2.0
prefix: ssm
title: Scout source management
---
[ssm] Generalize scout source onboarding and indexing (planning)
A single scout command replaces the current per-vendor pattern (a bespoke
fetch_modal_docs.py-shaped script per source, a hand-added tuple in
search.py's DOCS_SOURCES, a manual search.py --update run). One command
registers a new remote source with a TTL, fetches it, and indexes it; the
same command re-fetches and re-indexes any already-registered source whose
TTL has expired, replacing today's read-the-warning-then-copy-the-refresh-
command manual loop.
Vine graphs are workspace-authored planning artifacts scout never indexes
today; add them as a first-class chunked corpus alongside spec/notes/
proposals/docs, using structural (per-task) chunking rather than raw word
windows, since a task is already the natural retrievable unit.
-> ssm/design/command-surface
-> ssm/design/source-registry
-> ssm/design/vine-chunking
-> ssm/design/vine-corpus
-> ssm/implement/source-command
-> ssm/implement/vine-indexing
---
[ssm/design/source-registry] Design a generic source descriptor (notstarted)
Replace the ad hoc DOCS_SOURCES tuple (vendor name, mirror dir) and the
one-off per-vendor fetch script (fetch_modal_docs.py's llms.txt-walk-and-
mirror logic) with a single descriptor shape covering every source kind
scout will fetch: name, origin URL, ttl_days, fetch strategy (e.g.
llms-txt-mirror, arxiv/openreview pdf, future kinds), and the artifact path
under resources/. The descriptor is the registry entry; sources.json (via
freshness.py) remains the fetched-state ledger, not the registry itself.
No new source-specific script should need to be hand-written after this
lands -- adding a source is filling in a descriptor, not authoring code.
---
[ssm/design/vine-chunking] Design per-task chunking for vine files (notstarted)
A .vine file is a structured task graph, not prose -- word-windowing it like
a markdown file would split a task's id/name/description/decisions across
arbitrary chunk boundaries and return a self-citing id that names no real
unit. Design a chunker that parses each vine into its task blocks (reusing
bacchus's vine parser semantics: id, name, status, description, decisions)
and emits one chunk per task, self-citing as "<vine-stem>#<task-id>#vine"
(or similar), including ref blocks. A task whose description exceeds
comfortable embedding length may still need internal windowing -- decide
whether that stays out of scope for the first cut or is handled by
sub-chunking within a task while preserving the task-id citation.
---
[ssm/design/vine-corpus] Decide where vine chunks attach in search.py (notstarted)
Given per-task chunking from ssm/design/vine-chunking, decide which corpus
absorbs vine chunks. Vines are workspace-authored planning text (like spec/
notes/proposals), not third-party material and not vendor docs, so the
workspace corpus is the default candidate -- confirm no separation concern
(a vine task chunk competing against spec/proposal prose in the same
ranked results) forces a fourth corpus instead. Wire the chosen glob
(root localmodal.vine, proposals/**/*.vine, any future vine locations)
into workspace_chunks() alongside the existing spec/notes/proposals/doc
sources, using the chunker from ssm/design/vine-chunking rather than the
existing word-window helper.
-> ssm/design/vine-chunking
---
[ssm/implement/source-command] Implement the generalized add/refresh command (notstarted)
Build the single command from ssm/design/source-registry: given a
descriptor (new source) or no argument (scan sources.json for TTL-expired
or artifact-absent entries via freshness.warnings_for), fetch each and
stamp it via freshness.stamp, then run search.py's update path so the
result is searchable immediately. This supersedes fetch_modal_docs.py and
any future per-vendor script as the onboarding path -- once this lands,
no ancestor task or doc should still instruct a user to write a new
vendor-specific fetch script; existing vendor scripts may be kept working
underneath as fetch-strategy implementations, but are no longer the
public entry point for adding a source.
-> ssm/design/command-surface
-> ssm/design/source-registry
---
[ssm/implement/vine-indexing] Implement vine parsing and corpus wiring (notstarted)
Implement the per-task chunker designed in ssm/design/vine-chunking and
wire it into workspace_chunks() per the attachment point decided in
ssm/design/vine-corpus. Confirm docs_search/workspace_search-style self-
citing ids resolve back to a real task via vine_read, the same way a
paper/doc citation resolves back to its source page.
-> ssm/design/vine-corpus
---
[ssm/design/command-surface] Design the scout command surface (notstarted)
Before any implementation starts, carefully design and encapsulate the actual surface a caller invokes: is it a scout MCP tool, a resources/ CLI script, or both; its exact argument shape (new-source descriptor vs. no-argument refresh scan); its output/error contract; and how it stays isolated from the fetch-strategy internals in ssm/design/source-registry so a new fetch strategy never changes the calling contract.
Accept: the owner confirms one settled invocation surface and argument/output contract before ssm/implement/source-command begins.
-> ssm/design/source-registry
